<h1 class="hero-h">A 90-day AI rollout plan <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">for mid-market operators.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">This is the operations-focused companion to the AI implementation roadmap — the week-by-week checklist for the operator (COO, Chief of Staff, Head of Ops) actually running the rollout. Less strategy, more checklist.</p>
</div></div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Who this is for</span><h2 class="h2">The operator who has to run it</h2><p class="body">Your CEO has said yes to AI. Now you have to make it happen. This checklist is the version you can print, tape to your monitor, and check off as you go.</p><div class="callout"><p>The rollout fails the same way the strategy fails — too many things tried at once, nobody owning execution. If you have to choose between doing all of this and doing the first 30% well, choose the 30%.</p></div></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Days 1-30</span><h2 class="h2">Setup &amp; first win</h2><ul class="checklist"><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>CEO has stated the goal in writing — one paragraph, shared with the company.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>One named AI lead, 8-12 hrs/week minimum, with calendar protected.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>Audit of current AI usage complete (paid licenses + shadow IT).</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>Top 10 candidate workflows inventoried and ranked by leverage.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>Top 3 workflows selected — with named workflow owner per workflow.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>Enterprise AI platform selected and seats provisioned for affected users.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>Data classification rules confirmed: what can go into AI tools, what cannot.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>First workflow shipped — actually used in production, not just demoed.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>Measured baseline for first workflow recorded (time, output, quality).</span></li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Days 31-60</span><h2 class="h2">Two more workflows</h2><ul class="checklist"><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>Workflow #2 in production with named owner and weekly review cadence.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>Workflow #3 in production with named owner and weekly review cadence.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>Measured impact recorded for workflows #1, #2, and #3 (time saved, cycle time).</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>Weekly office hours with the AI lead established and attended.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>Internal Slack channel or equivalent for sharing prompts and patterns.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>First playbook documented: "How we use AI for [workflow #1]" — stored where everyone can find it.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>Identified at least one workflow that should NOT use AI yet and documented why.</span></li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Days 61-90</span><h2 class="h2">Scale &amp; govern</h2><ul class="checklist"><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>Adjacent workflows shipped (2-3 expansions of existing workflows).</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>All-team training session held — workflow owners present what they built.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>One-page AI Usage Policy published and emailed to the team.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>Q2 priority workflows selected with owners assigned.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>First 90-day impact review prepared for CEO/exec team: hours saved, cycle time changes, revenue impact (if any), next quarter ask.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>Vendor relationships established (your CSM at the AI platform has your number).</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>Backlog of next-quarter workflows triaged and prioritized.</span></li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Risk register</span><h2 class="h2">What to watch for and how to respond</h2><div class="table-wrap"><table class="t"><thead><tr><th>Risk</th><th>Signal</th><th>Response</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Adoption stalls at the AI lead</td><td>Only the AI lead uses the tools. Workflows have not transferred to owners.</td><td>Schedule pair-sessions: AI lead works alongside the workflow owner until owner is solo for 3 consecutive uses.</td></tr><tr><td>Quality drift</td><td>Customer complaints, brand voice slips, factual errors in outputs.</td><td>Add a human-review checkpoint before any output ships. Audit 10 random outputs weekly.</td></tr><tr><td>Data leakage</td><td>Confidential information appears in shared chats or non-approved tools.</td><td>Suspend access. Notify owner. Issue refresher on data classifications. Document incident.</td></tr><tr><td>Cost overrun</td><td>Per-seat or per-token costs growing faster than usage value.</td><td>Move from per-token model to a fixed-seat tier. Audit which seats are actually used.</td></tr><tr><td>Team pushback</td><td>Visible resistance, "I prefer doing it myself" comments.</td><td>Investigate. Usually a sign the tool is being forced into a workflow it does not fit. Adjust scope, not pressure.</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div></section>

